      "content": "dude you're literally repeating the same mistake. \n\n`self.parent = [i for i in range(n)]` is just going to create a list of 1 million Python integer objects. In Python, an integer object is about 28 bytes, and the list itself holds pointers (8 bytes each). That's maybe 36MB just for one list. With `self.rank` and the edge list and everything else, you're gonna blow past 64MB way before you even start the loop.\n\nyou can't just use standard lists and call it a day. you need a way to bypass the high memory overhead of Python objects. look into `array.array` or something like that, or maybe some other way to keep the memory footprint tiny so the judge doesn't kill it. just make it work within 64MB.",
